The Moreau series, by S. Andrew Swann. Picked it up when I saw a cover show up in a google image search for "anthro pulp sci-fi covers".

I just started book 3 out of 4. Good, but very little /hmofa/ in it so far. They seem to be pairing the female rabbit main character of this book with a fox guy. Here's hoping that is either a mislead, or he becomes a cooler character as the book goes on.

The anthros themselves are from various supersoldier programs. After the production of modified humans quickly became illegal in most places, countries switched to the questionable but not yet illegal animal manipulation to make troops. Each country had a different program. For example the Indian tigers are the big scary top of the line models, while South American countries went with quantity over quality with their rats and rabbits. Though by the time the book takes place, many are 2nd or 3rd generation and weren't born into military service like their parents.
There are also still the rare gene modded humans from places that aren't as strict with their rules running around.
